7.3.25  12:58 pm   "futuristic" has nothing to do with the future, it's a style movement that started in the 60s, but now we design things to look futuristic because it reminds us of old movies about the future. What do you think of this? 

      i think that would be pinning down a perfectly useful word too tightly. having any connotation with the time period you mentioned, is not something i feel the word would still carry by default. there's no reason the word 'futuristic' should not be still generally available to mean 'of or relating to the future' and i think anyone can easily get away with using it this way in conversation, and be immediately understood
